                                         JOHANNESBURG - A KwaZulu-Natal police officer has shot his wife before turning the gun on himself during a domestic dispute. It’s understood the incident took place at a Catholic mission, where the woman had been preparing Sunday meals. The officer allegedly got into an argument with his wife before he fired three shots at her. He then took his own life. Spokesperson for Reaction Unit South Africa Prem Balram says the woman was rushed to a hospital. “He was declared dead at the scene by paramedics. His wife was rushed to a hospital after sustaining a gunshot wound on her arm.” (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)